com.sap.spc.product

Interface IProductEngine


  • public interface IProductEngine
    Interface the product engine. The product engine provides all methods for accessing product related data.

        Returns:
        the new instance or null if no data was found in the database

      • getSPCProductByExternalID

        ISPCProduct getSPCProductByExternalID(java.lang.String productID,
                                      java.lang.String productLogSys,
                                      java.lang.String productType)
                               throws ProductInconsistentDBException
        Create a new instance. The parameters marked as optional can be set to null.
        Parameters:
        productID - the external ID of the product to be created
        productLogSys - the logical system where the product was maintained (may be null)
        productType - the type of the product, eg. "01" (may be null)
        Returns:
        the new instance or null if no data was found in the database
        Throws:
        SPCIllegalArgumentException - if conversionEngine or productID is null
        ConversionInconsistentDBException - if a unit of measure is not found in the database
        SPCProductIdentifierNotUnique - if the external Product ID is not unique and LogSys/type have not been specified.
        ProductInconsistentDBException

      • getSPCProducts

        ISPCProduct[] getSPCProducts(java.lang.String productGUID,
                             java.lang.String productID,
                             java.lang.String productLogSys,
                             java.lang.String productType)
                      throws ProductInconsistentDBException
        Creates new instances. The parameters marked as optional can be set to null.
        Parameters:
        productGUID - the internal ID of the product to be created (optional)
        productID - the external ID of the product to be created (optional); SQL wildcards (%, [], ^, _) can be used
        productLogSys - the logical system where the product was maintained (may be null)
        productType - the type of the product, eg. "01" (may be null)
        Returns:
        an array of new instances or an array of zero length if no data was found in the database
        Throws:
        SPCIllegalArgumentException - if conversionEngine or productID is null
        ConversionInconsistentDBException - if a unit of measure is not found in the database
        ProductInconsistentDBException

                             java.lang.String logicalSystem,
                             java.lang.String productType)
                      throws ProductInconsistentDBException
        Creates new instances. The parameters marked as optional can be set to null. This method is intended to be used by the condition selection dialog.
        Parameters:
        productID - the external ID of the product to be created; SQL wildcards (%, [], ^, _) can be used
        productLogSys - the logical system where the product was maintained (may be null)
        productType - the type of the product, eg. "01" (may be null)
        Returns:
        an array of new instances or an array of zero length if no data was found in the database
        Throws:
        SPCIllegalArgumentException - if conversionEngine or productID is null
        ConversionInconsistentDBException - if a unit of measure is not found in the database
        ProductInconsistentDBException
